news.title: Nagpur civic body offers up to 10% rebate on property tax payments till December 31
news.para: Launched under the guidance of Municipal Commissioner and Administrator Abhijeet Chaudhari, the scheme also offers a 5% rebate to property holders opting for offline payments.

news.title: Hyderabad: ED summons Vamsiram Builders, others in Bhoodan land case
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate has summoned key developers, including B Subba Reddy and Marri Janardhan Reddy, in a land case linked to IAS officer Amoy Kumar. The investigation centers on 50 acres of Bhoodan land in Nagaram village, with the ED probing potential fraudulent transactions.

news.title: Odisha RERA stops builder from booking flats over flouting norms
news.para: ORERA has also asked the promoter to immediately hand over the common areas to the association and register the sale deeds with buyers for units already sold.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body asks builders to start allotment of EWS, LIG flats
news.para: In the meeting held on Friday with integrated township developers, the department asked developers about the delay and asked them to complete the allotments within two weeks, failing which GDA would refuse a completion certificate to the developers.

news.title: Mumbai: Property tax dues can be paid at CFCs till midnight of December 31
news.para: The civic authority has collected Rs 3,582 crore, reaching 58% of its Rs 6,200 crore target for the current financial year. The CFC offices typically close at 6 pm.

news.title: UltraTech to acquire minority stake in Star Cement
news.para: ​The development comes three days after the Aditya Birla group firm completed the acquisition of a controlling stake in India Cements Ltd, turning the south-based company into its subsidiary.

news.title: Mohali district revenue officer appointed nodal officer for plot registration in unauthorized colonies
news.para: To facilitate people with the policy of the Punjab govt to provide relief to plot holders (up to 500 square yards) for registration of their plots situated in an unauthorised colony, the Mohali deputy commissioner (DC) Aashika Jain has designated district revenue officer Amandeep Chawla as the nodal officer.

news.title: Mohali civic body starts drive against illegal constructions
news.para: An unauthorised construction was demolished at Mataur and Kumbran villages of Mohali on Thursday, said MC commissioner T Benith.

news.title: Gurugram civic body resolves property ID, park funds complaints at samadhan camp
news.para: A resident's long-standing issue regarding property IDs was finally settled. Moreover, officials addressed a pending grievance from a Palam Vihar RWA concerning the delayed disbursement of park maintenance funds.

news.title: Pune metro line III completion likely to be delayed till September 2025
news.para: Pune Metropolitan Region Development Authority (PMRDA) officials said that the concessionaire has requested for revised timelines from the earlier target of March 2025.

news.title: Property cards to be distributed under Swamitva scheme in 376 villages of Nagpur division
news.para: Beneficiaries from six districts in the division will receive their property cards, officially recognising their ownership of ancestral and residential properties.

news.title: Lucknow development body to begin registration for Edu City plots soon
news.para: Officials have revealed plans for an international-level university and state-of-the-art infrastructure. The first phase will offer plots in four sectors (3, 4, 6, and 7) with sizes ranging from 400 to 3,200 sq ft.

news.title: Delhi LG directs DDA to extend single-window special camps for PM-UDAY till March 2025
news.para: During these eight days, 1,152 conveyance deeds/authorisation slips were issued, and 283 properties were registered by the sub-registrars, providing final ownership rights to the property holders, the statement added.

news.title: Over 41 lakh people in Uttar Pradesh to benefit from Pradhan Mantri SVAMITVA Yojana
news.para: To note, SVAMITVA is a scheme of the Ministry of Panchayati Raj that provides a ‘Record of Rights' to village household owners.

news.title: Chennai development body to e-auction plots along Outer Ring Road in January
news.para: CMDA aims to develop CORR into a vibrant economic corridor featuring premium housing, industries, warehousing, hotels and urban forests, with areas such as Minjur, Red Hills, Poonamallee, and Vandalur integrated with the third master plan.

news.title: Greater Noida: GNIDA files FIR against 18 people over illegal housing projects in Tusyana
news.para: These projects encroached on govt land, caused revenue loss to the govt, and deceived customers by offering plots and flats at cheaper rates.

news.title: Maharashtra looks to boost builders' participation in e-registration process for first sale flats
news.para: The initiative aimed at reducing footfall at registration offices by enabling the buyers to complete the online registration process from the developers' offices in coordination with the property registration department.
